    "summary": "Second-year MA student in International Security at Sciences Po Paris School of International Affairs with the Enhanced Master option in Peace and War Studies and a concentration in Middle Eastern Studies. I am currently undertaking a Policy internship at the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons, where I primarily contribute to drafting policies and strategies for the Fifth Review Conference of the Chemical Weapons Convention and other issues, inter-agency cooperation and project management. Previous experience in the defence sector in Brussels, with specific attention to the issue of military interoperability among European armed forces. Graduated with 110 cum Laude in International Studies from the University of Trento with a focus on international organizations and a final dissertation on the implications of the energy transition on oil- and gas-producing countries in the MENA region. \n\nParticularly passionate about security and defence, conflict prevention and resolution, political-military strategy, arms control, disarmament and non-proliferation (ADN), with a distinct interest in the Middle East and Africa. Strong organizational, analytical and interpersonal skills and multi-stakeholder management developed throughout my career.",
